It turned out that with the USB-C breakout I used to connect the charger, 5V and GND were swapped on the Silkscreen.
I swapped the cables and now the charging indicator is lighting up.
The ESP didn't go online immediately. Let's wait a few minutes.
One hour is over and it's still offline.
It looks like it's restarting and triggering a Tasmota reset function.
I think the panel is simply not good enough. I've now ordered a bigger one and hope that it will work then.
Take a look at what I've found in my workshop.
A 24-V panel. Unfortunately, the sun is already so low (and is partially obstructed by a tree) that the value practically drops to zero as soon as I put the device into operation.
I'll probably have to wait until tomorrow to see if it's sufficient for this setup or if I need the better panel that I ordered.
